  "texts": [
    "If issues are identified, the Code Teacher analyzes the bug reports and the buggy code, subsequently providing repair instructions to address the errors.",
    "Self-repair [102] and TGen [96] refine code by utilizing feedback obtained from running pre-defined test cases.When predefined test cases are unavailable, the Tester can generate a variety of test cases, ranging from common scenarios to edge cases.",
    "These tests help uncover subtle issues that might otherwise go unnoticed and provide actionable feedback to guide subsequent refinement iterations [53,54,56,117].Some frameworks employ the Information Retriever to gather relevant information to assist code generation.",
    "For instance, Agent4PLC [87] and MapCoder [57] incorporate a Retrieval Agent tasked with sourcing examples of similar problems and extracting related knowledge.",
    "This agent provides essential contextual information and references tailored to the user's input, ensuring that solutions are well-informed and adhere to domain-specific best practices."
